Description: length ball at 123 kph seaming in toward middle, Shaw shuffles across to flick through square leg for one.
length ball angled wide outside off, goes to cut and misses.
fullish length on sixth stump, slaps this 123 kph delivery in the gap between mid-off and extra cover to the rope.
short on seventh stump, cuts this crisply but straight to cover.
back of a length pitching on leg stump, angled away toward off, defended behind point.
length ball outside off, slapped to cover, diving stop by Rahul turns four into one.
fullish length ball on sixth stump, goes to drive over mid-off and splices this off the outer half of the bat floating just wide of mid-off tracking right landing a yard out of reach for a single.
133 kph delivery lands back of a length on off, superb back foot punch timed behind point to the rope.
back of a length into the hips, goes back to flick this 133 kph delivery into midwicket for one.
short on fourth stump at 129 kph, pulled firmly through midwicket to the rope. Ganguly and Ponting nod approvingly in the dugout.
length ball on fifth stump, short arm jab pull dragged through wide midwicket for two.
back of a length on the hips, flicked to deep fine leg and beats the diving fielder to the rope.
length ball on fifth stump, cracks this flat to cover on the ring for none.

another jackknife!Good length ball on leg stump, Warner goes to pull and then has to adjust late to toe slap drag this to long-on for one. Identical ball to the one that dismissed Mayers but Warner is able to keep this out.
good length ball on off, punched to extra cover for none.
length ball on fourth stump, Rossouw shaped to reverse then goes back orthodox and slaps this back to the bowler.
full on the legs, goes back to flick through long-on for one.
knee high full toss on the legs, miscues a heave to deep backward square leg trickling along the ground for one.
length ball on middle, pulled to deep midwicket, one-handed diving effort by the fielder out there but he's only able to parry it wider to the rope.
charges a low full toss and swings over this deflecting off his shins to short third for none.
short on leg stump, pulls this flat to long-on for one.
googly lands on a good length on middle, swishes across this and is beaten.
good length ball on fourth stump, goes back to punch to the cover sweeper for one.

full on leg stump, shuffles well across the stumps and goes to sweep and misses off the pads/shoes, huge lbw shout denied and the ball pops up off a deflection of some kind behind the wicket for a catch claimed by the short fine leg fielder. Looked pretty stone dead live.LSG have gone for a review. Rossouw has started marching off without even waiting for the replays.Nothing on bat or glove on the initial shot but the ball has popped up off the bat of the bat on the follow through in bizarre fashion and a catch was taken by the fielder coming over from short fine leg. We're not even going to get to the ball-tracking for lbw because he's been given out caught.
full on the stumps at 145 kph, driven to long-on for two.
145 kph lands full and well outside leg stump, flicked to deep backward square leg for two.
back of a length on the stumps, flicked into midwicket for one.
143 kph delivery lands back of a length on fifth stump, guided with an open face to deep third for one.
back of a length on off, Warner with another short arm jab pull flat toward deep square leg, fielded on a bounce for one.
146 kph good length ball on fifth stump beats Powell prodding forward.
short on middle, goes to pull and bottom edges it into his thigh.
good length ball on middle, defended back to the bowler.
good length ball on the stumps, pushed into point for one.

99 kph googly skids on from a good length on fourth stump and zings Powell in front of middle stump on the back foot playing back to punch through midwicket. He read the googly but it just came onto him far quicker than he expected and he's too late getting the bat down. Big lbw shout upheld. Powell marches off without a moment's thought for a review. It was stone dead.
full on sixth stump, drives uppishly to long-off for one.
full on leg stump, flicked through midwicket for one.
length ball on fifth stump, pumps this on the up over cover to the rope.
back of a length cutter angled into the legs, Warner through a flick too early before it caroms into cover for an extra.
length ball on fifth stump, swats this high but gently short of long-on for one.
length ball on fourth stump, pulled to wide long-on for twoto bring up a 45-ball half-century. Incredibly, it's his 56th half-century in his prolific IPL career.
slower length ball outside leg stump, Warner premeditates a reverse scoop and keeps the hand back long enough to get it wide of the keeper to the third man rope.
short ball on the stumps, gets on his toes to swat this through wide midwicket for two.
length ball swatted through square leg for two.
full on the legs at 132 kph, goes to whip this away but is late.
bounced out!Short ball on the stumps at 136 kph, goes to pull and is hustled for pace top edging this high behind the stumps. Keeper Pooran shuffles in front of short fine leg for the take.
back of a length on fifth stump, guided to backward point for none.
full on the stumps, driven to long-on for one.
slower ball lands full on seventh stump, Warner miscues a drive skying this to long-on. Simple catch taken three yards inside the rope by K Gowtham.
length ball outside off, slapped through cover for one.
good length ball on fifth stump, pushes at this and misses.
full on middle, reaches forward to scoop this over the keeper, gets under it more than he wanted and it goes almost straight up before landing between short fine leg and short third for one.
length ball on sixth stump slapped to the cover sweeper for one.
good length ball on fourth stump, leans back to slap to backward point for none.
full on fifth stump, reaches a long way to sweep this through square leg for one.
length ball on off stump, flicked through wide midwicket for two.
length ball on seventh stump, slapped to the point sweeper for one.
full and wide, drives inside out over wide extra cover to the rope.
Axar isn't giving up!Fullish length on middle and leg, heaves this over wide midwicket landing past the LCD ad boards.
slower ball on a good length on fifth stump at 123 kph, goes for another heave but through the shot early.
length ball wide outside off, toe slaps this through the ring for one.
misfires on the yorker sending down a knee high full toss at 131 kph, slapped to long-on for one.
charges a yorker this time and scuffs it into the ground back to Unadkat.
full on off, drives inside out to long-off for one.
knee high full toss flicked flat to deep backward square leg for one.
slower length ball on fifth stump, goes to cut and misses.
fullish length ball on eighth stump, Kuldeep backs away from leg but takes himself out of reach to get bat on ball with a late stab.

It's Wood's night for sure!Leg stump half-volley flicked effortlessly but picks out deep square leg. Sub fielder Mankad takes a simple catch at chest height four yards inside the rope. Not as spectacular a delivery as his previous three wicket-taking balls but still effective nonetheless.
full in the slot on fifth stump, drives this inside out over mid-off to the rope. First boundary conceded by Wood in this match.
back of a length on fourth stump, goes to pull and misses.
bouncer on leg stump, ducked under to leave alone.

Wood has a five-for after making the switch to LSG!Length ball outside leg stump, Sakariya tries to heave this over the leg side but is rushed and it flutters up off the splice of the bat to Krunal at short midwicket inside the ring. Simple catch.
144 kph lands full and searing in toward leg stump, but Mukesh is able to keep this out backing away from leg stump with a punch to cover.The match ends with a whimper as LSG march to a 50-run win.
Half-tracker on the hips, Shaw swivels and clobbers this over backward square leg, one bounce over the rope.
another short ball on middle this time, pulled to deep midwicket for one.

Warner goes to reverse sweep this fullish length ball on middle and gets hit in the family jewels... Big lbw shout denied. Warner is not the only one speechless, but for different reasons to everyone else watching.
short on middle, backs away and goes to cut, picks out backward point.
short on middle, pulls this fiercely over square leg and wide midwicket on the rope has no chance.
length ball on fifth stump, goes to cut and bottom edges this to cover.
length ball at 133 kph on fourth stump, Shaw shuffles back and across to flick into the leg side.
length ball angled across seventh stump at 135 kph, goes to cut and misses.
full on seventh stump, miscues a drive to extra cover.
short on the stumps, goes to pull and toes this tamely to midwicket for none.
length ball on sixth stump, goes to cut and another toe-edged shot goes behind point for two.
137 kph length ball on sixth stump, goes to cut and bottom edges this past the stumps to the fine leg rope.
short ball on middle, goes back to defend.
back of a length on fourth stump, defended on the back foot to cover.

bullseye! Wood rattles the off stump wood at 147 kph!Bowled on a good length angled in from wide of the crease, Shaw's feet never move and he flails at this tamely. He's beaten badly and the bails go flying.

double bullseye! Another 147 kph bullet leaves a big dent in off stump about three-quarters of the way up!Marsh shuffled across to cover his stumps and goes for an expansive drive to a ball pitching on fifth stump but is beaten by the sharp inward movement.
length ball on fifth stump, goes to drive this and a thick edge goes behind to the keeper. Free hit though so no harm done.
length ball on fourth stump, defended into the off side for none.
length ball on fifth stump, slapped to cover for none.
yorker on middle, jammed out back to Avesh who fields with his right hand and looks at the bandaging on there again.
132 kph length ball on fourth stump, pulled through square leg for one.
length ball on seventh stump, pulls this fiercely over midwicket. One bounce over the rope.
fullish length ball on seventh stump, goes to drive and is beaten.
fullish length ball on fifth stump angled in, pokes at this awkwardly and is beaten.
back of a length on middle, Warner hops back to defend this 148 kph delivery.
good length ball on middle, defended watchfully again by Warner to mid-off.
short on off stump, cuts this to deep point for one.
back of a length angled into off at 140 kph, defended hopping on his toes to prod this to cover.
back of a length on sixth stump, defended to cover.

Sarfaraz can't escape the short ball from Wood!Banged in short at 137 kph, Sarfaraz ducks and almost falls over getting out of the way of the ball... before bizarrely changing his mind in a split second as he's losing his balance and tries to attack this with an uppercut over the keeper. He gets plenty of bat on it, enough for it to sail to deep fine leg who is fielding very straight and takes a chest high catch three yards in from the rope.
good length ball on sixth stump, cut to backward point for none.
length ball on sixth stump, cuts this to deep point for one.
full on the stumps, driven to long-on for one.
length ball on sixth stump, cuts this late to backward point. Rahul fumbles this to turn a dot into one.
full on middle, defended to cover.
charges a length ball before adjusting getting nowhere near the pitch and swats this through extra cover for one.
good length ball on fifth stump, slapped through the off side for one.
good length ball on leg stump, grips in the pitch and checks this back uppishly to the bowler.
back of a length angled into the legs outside leg, punched through extra cover for one.
short on middle, pulled through wide midwicket for one.
full on middle, chipped to long-on for one.
good length ball speared quicker into the legs, goes to flick but misses.
length ball on fifth stump, backs away and cracks this through wide extra cover beating the sweeper to the rope.
short on seventh stump, slapped straight to cover but a misfield by Krunal allows a single.
good length ball pulled on one knee through square leg for one.
full on leg stump, Rossouw steps away from leg to create room to stroke this high over the bowler to the long-on rope.

thigh high full toss on the hips, heaves this toward Unadkat at deep backward square leg. He takes a chest high catch...but was stepping on the rope and didn't flick it up to himself before he had made contact with the foam triangle.Unadkat didn't realize how close he was to the rope.
full on the legs, driven off Bishnoi to long-off for one.
